  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the <strong>ginger</strong> (no need to peel!) into rounds</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599494090794-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599494090794-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599494090794-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599494090794-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599494090794-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Season the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and add them to a cold, dry pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid)</p><p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, then add the <strong>brown rice</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>ginger </strong>to the pan with the chicken</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1599494101594-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1599494101594-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1599494101594-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1599494101594-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1599494101594-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pour over 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to a boil, covered, over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and simmer, turning the chicken half way, for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599494117054-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599494117054-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599494117054-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599494117054-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599494117054-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, slice the<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> to a tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the mushrooms are cooked and starting to crisp – these are your <strong>roasted mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599494127309-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599494127309-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599494127309-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599494127309-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599494127309-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>cracked black pepper </strong>(not a fan of pepper? Go easy!), <strong>soy sauce</strong> and<strong> rice vinegar </strong>– this is your <strong>turmeric stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599494137927-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599494137927-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599494137927-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599494137927-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599494137927-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board – this is your <strong>poached chicken</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>turmeric stock</strong> to the pan, bring to the boil over a high heat, and cook, covered, for 3-5 min further or until the rice is cooked and tender – this is your<strong> turmeric, ginger & rice broth</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if the rice has soaked up a lot of broth!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599494150598-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599494150598-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599494150598-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599494150598-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599494150598-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then add the <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p><p>Finely slice the <strong>poached chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646222161846-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646222161846-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646222161846-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646222161846-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646222161846-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced poached chicken</strong>, <strong>roasted mushrooms </strong>and<strong> wilted spinach</strong> over the <strong>turmeric, ginger & rice broth</strong></p><p>Tip: Remove the sliced ginger rounds!</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
